“When I first hear about COVID-19 outbreak, I didn’t go out of my house for a week, I was afraid. I have to spend more money to buy masks to protect ourselves, supplements, eggs, and milk to strengthen our immune system. But as a coconut sugar farmer, I’m grateful that my income wasn’t affected and I feel safe. I couldn’t imagine if I still insisted to continue living in the city and then the COVID-19 pandemic hit. I don't know what our fate would be. My husband would automatically be furloughed, then my child's school would also be closed. I am grateful I decided to return to my hometown, and become a coconut sugar farmer," shares Ponisih. 

